🚀 Kanban Board

A modern, responsive Kanban Board web app to manage tasks efficiently. Supports adding, editing, deleting tasks, priority indicators, and light/dark theme switching. All data is stored locally using localStorage.

🌟 Features

Three Columns: TODO, DOING, DONE

Task Management: Add, edit, delete tasks with title, description, status, and priority

Priority Indicators:

Low 🟢

Medium 🟡

High 🔴

Responsive Design: Mobile-friendly layout with floating action buttons

Theme Switch: Light/Dark mode with saved preference

Local Storage: Tasks persist across browser sessions


No backend needed. Everything runs in the browser.

🛠 Usage

Add a Task: Click "+ Add New Task" (desktop) or the floating "+" (mobile). Fill details and click Create Task.

Edit a Task: Click a task card, modify details, click Save Changes.

Delete a Task: Open task → click Delete Task.

Toggle Theme: Use the sidebar switch to change between light and dark modes.

Sidebar Toggle: Hide or show sidebar on desktop using Hide Sidebar / 👀 button.

📁 File Structure
kanban-board/
│
├─ index.html        # HTML layout
├─ styles.css        # Styles, themes, and responsive design
├─ scripts.js        # Task logic, modals, and theme management
└─ README.md         # Project documentation

⚡ Technologies

HTML5 – Semantic structure

CSS3 – Styling, responsive design, themes

JavaScript (ES6+) – Task handling, modals, localStorage, and theme toggle

🔑 Key JS Features

Dynamic task rendering in respective columns

LocalStorage persistence for tasks and theme

Modal windows for adding and editing tasks

Event listeners for sidebar, task cards, and theme toggle

Automatic theme detection (system preference)

🚀 Future Improvements

Drag-and-drop tasks

Multiple boards support

Task due dates & reminders

Export/import tasks as JSON

